{title: Echoes From The Burning Bush}
{artist: Chuck Wagon
Gang}
{composer: Written by Bryon Foust and V.O. Summar}

[G]Moses stood on holy ground
[C]Far from God descended down
[G]Set the roadside bush on [D7]fire (bush on fire)
[G]Then the Lord did there explain
[C]Through His servant should remain
[G]All the echoes from the [D7]bush on [G]fire (the [C]bush on [G]fire)

Oh I can hear those lovely echoes [C]from the [G]burning bush
How they [D7]thrill my [G]soul (how they [C]thrill my [G]soul
Oh I can hear those thrilling echoes [C]from the [G]burning bush
Point me [A7]to the [D7]goal (point me to the goal)
[G]I no more am doubting but with joy I'm shouting
With no thought of shame to blush (no [D7]shame to [G]blush)
This my song shall ever be [C]words that are so sweet to me
[G]Echoes from the [A7]burn[D7]ing [G]bush (the burning bush)
God sent down His only Son
[C]Just to ransom everyone
[G]By the echoes from the [D7]fire (from the fire)
[G]God of every earthly land
[C]Would not pick nor choose a man
[G]For His blood will save us [D7]from the [G]fire (eternal fire)
Repeat #2,3